  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      First, fix a segfault in <command>shuf</command> program:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>patch -p1 -i ../coreutils-&coreutils-version;-shuf_segfault-1.patch</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      POSIX requires that programs from coreutils recognize character boundaries
      correctly even in multibyte locales. The following patch fixes this
      non-compliance and other internationalization-related bugs: 
    </para>

<screen><userinput>patch -p1 -i ../coreutils-&coreutils-version;-i18n-4.patch</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install the package by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>FORCE_UNSAFE_CONFIGURE=1 \
./configure --disable-nls \
            --enable-no-install-program=kill,uptime &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <parameter>FORCE_UNSAFE_CONFIGURE=1</parameter>: This allows compilation
        to be run as root.
      </para>

      <para>
        <parameter>--enable-no-install-program=kill,uptime</parameter>: The
        purpose of this switch is to prevent coreutils from installing binaries
        that are installed by other packages.
      </para>

    </sect3>

  </sect2>

